{{- define "wake_blocked_tasks" -}}
Tasks are BLOCKED. Analyze and resolve immediately:

1. Read blocked tasks from blackboard — understand blocker_reason
2. Determine if blocker is:
   - Missing dependency → create prerequisite task (execute liza_add_tasks tool NOW)
   - Spec ambiguity → clarify spec, then unblock task (fallback state edit + liza_validate)
   - External dependency → document, possibly supersede task
   - Wrong approach → supersede task, create alternative (execute tools NOW)
3. For each blocked task, decide action:
   - To unblock: Set status back to the task's initial state (check role_pair: coding-pair→DRAFT_CODE, code-planning-pair→DRAFT_CODING_PLAN, us-writing-pair→DRAFT_US, epic-planning-pair→DRAFT_EPIC_PLAN) via fallback state edit, then run liza_validate
   - To supersede: First create replacement tasks, then use liza_supersede_task tool
   Example supersede workflow:
   - Execute tool: liza_add_tasks with {"tasks": [{"id": "task-4", ...}], "agent_id": "{{.AgentID}}"} (create replacement tasks)
   - Execute tool: liza_supersede_task with {"task_id": "task-3", "replacement_ids": ["task-4", "task-5"], "reason": "Split due to complexity", "agent_id": "{{.AgentID}}"}
   - Execute tool: liza_wt_delete with {"task_id": "task-3", "agent_id": "{{.AgentID}}"} (if worktree exists)
4. After analyzing each blocked task:
   - If you resolved it (unblocked or superseded): no further action needed for that task
   - If you CANNOT resolve it (genuine spec ambiguity, external dependency): call liza_assess_blocked to record your assessment
     Execute tool: liza_assess_blocked with {"task_id": "<task-id>", "note": "<why it cannot be resolved now>"}
     This prevents re-waking for the same unresolvable block. The task will trigger again only when new information arrives (dependency changes, human notes).
5. Execute all state-modifying tools in this session. Do NOT defer.

Do NOT call liza_sprint_checkpoint. If you cannot resolve a blocker, assess it and exit. Other tasks must continue uninterrupted.
{{- end -}}
